<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOWARD CROCKETT; WROTE COUNTRY MUSIC'S 'HONKY TONK MAN' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Howard Crockett, 69, who wrote country music's classic "Honky Tonk Man" and 
sang his last major hit himself -- "The Last Will and Testament of a Drinking 
Man," which became a success in 1973."Honky Tonk Man," recorded by Johnny 
Horton, first reigned atop the charts in 1956 and then in 1986 when Dwight 
Yoakum made it popular again. Crockett wrote more than 200 songs; four went 
gold, two platinum and one double platinum. In Fort Worth, Tex., on Tuesday of 
lung cancer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
