<HEADLINE>
<P>
DAN HAMILTON; FOUNDING MEMBER OF '60S ROCK BAND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dan Hamilton, 49, a founder of the rock group Hamilton, Joe Frank and 
Reynolds, whose 1971 hit, "Don't Pull Your Love," rose to No. 4 on the charts 
and brought them a gold record.Formed in the late 1960s, the group comprised 
two guitarists and a keyboard player and made dozens of other recordings over 
the years, among them "Fallin' in Love" and "Winners and Losers," both in 1975. 
The group recently had been making a comeback in Las Vegas, where it was a 
popular lounge attraction. In Los Angeles on Dec. 22 of complications of 
abdominal surgery. 
</P>
</TEXT>
