<HEADLINE>
<P>
MILTON PITTS; WHITE HOUSE BARBER FOR FOUR PRESIDENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Milton Pitts, 82, who cut and styled the hair of four presidents.Working out 
of a small barbershop in the White House, Pitts cut the hair of Presidents 
Richard Nixon, Gerald Ford, Ronald Reagan and George Bush as well as other 
government VIPs. He also maintained a public shop near the Executive Mansion 
for 27 years. He interrupted his White House service during the Jimmy Carter 
Administration after he found himself paired with two imported hairstylists. He 
returned to cutting presidential hair after Reagan took office in 1981. It was 
Pitts who assured reporters that Reagan's hair, dark for a man in his 70s, was 
not dyed, as many had speculated. In Washington on Sunday of heart disease. 
</P>
</TEXT>
