COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: SANTA ANA; MATER DEI CHEERLEADERS: THEY'RE NO. 1, THEY'RE 
NO. 1 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON NALICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Usually cheerleaders shout and wave for the crowd, but at John Wayne Airport 
on Friday the crowd cheered for them. 
</P>
<P>
 The Mater Dei High School cheerleaders, returning from Dallas, where they won 
a national competition on Wednesday, received a hero's welcome from about 75 
jubilant family members and friends as they walked off the plane. 
</P>
<P>
 Varsity team captain Jennifer Boese, holding a three-foot-tall trophy, said 
the team went into the competition hoping to retain the National Cheerleaders 
Assn. championship title it won last year. 
</P>
<P>
 "We thought we were going to do pretty good, maybe finish in the top 10, but 
we were really happy to win again," she said. 
</P>
<P>
 The varsity song team also won first place in its category, and the junior 
varsity cheer team placed second in the nation. 
</P>
<P>
 The competition is the largest of its kind in the world, said team adviser 
John Merino. JON NALICK 
</P>
