<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY ALMANAC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The work schedule that closed county offices on alternate Fridays was ended in 
November by the county Board of Supervisors, who said the cost-savings did not 
justify the public inconvenience. 
</P>
<P>
 But in Irvine, city officials say a similar schedule begun in March has 
increased productivity, improved customer service by extending City Hall hours 
and saved the city about $56,000 in reduced operating costs. 
</P>
<P>
 With the reduction of 150 city employees over a three-year period, the work 
schedule makes better use of the remaining employees, according to city 
management analyst Mary Lou King. 
</P>
<P>
 "We have had no citizen complaints," King reported. Today 
</P>
<P>
 It's going to be a Humphrey Bogart kind of New Year's Eve party when Remick's 
Restaurant in Irvine is transformed into Rick's Cafe. 
</P>
<P>
 It's the annual event held by the Bogart & Bacall singles chapter of the 
Orange County Performing Arts Center. 
</P>
<P>
 The party is scheduled to run from 7:30 p.m. to 1 a.m. Casino gaming tables 
will complete the recreation of the nightclub made famous in the Bogart movie, 
"Casablanca." For information, call (714) 440-8833. 
</P>
