<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; HOLIDAY CLOSINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sunday is New Year's Day. The following will be closed Monday in observance of 
the holiday: 
</P>
<P>
 * All city, county, state and federal offices. 
</P>
<P>
 * County, state and federal courthouses. 
</P>
<P>
 * City and county libraries. 
</P>
<P>
 * Banks and savings and loans. 
</P>
<P>
 * Schools: There will be no classes Monday, and school offices, including 
those at colleges and universities, will be closed. 
</P>
<P>
 * Mail: There will be no mail delivery Monday. All post offices will be 
closed, and mail deposited in mailboxes will be picked up according to the 
posted holiday schedule. 
</P>
<P>
 * Trash: In most cities and unincorporated county areas, there will be no 
trash pickup Monday, and pickup will be one day late for the rest of the week. 
In Buena Park, Costa Mesa, La Habra, La Palma and Stanton, trash will be picked 
up on the regular schedule. In Anaheim, Brea, Garden Grove, Orange, Placentia 
and Yorba Linda, residents with trash pickup Monday should put their trash out 
Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 * Buses: Orange County Transportation Authority buses will run on a special 
holiday schedule Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 * Parks: All city- and county-run parks and recreation facilities will be 
closed Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
