<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAYBE IT WASN'T SUCH A BAD RAP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Avondre Jones (Dec. 18) can claim his USC basketball career didn't work out 
for a number of reasons, but the truth is that he just can't play a lick. The 
reason he didn't start or get much playing time last (season) was because he 
couldn't score, rebound, pass or play defense. 
</P>
<P>
 If his manager is correct that "he's just as good a rapper as he is a 
basketball player," he better start looking for a third career. 
</P>
<P>
 BOBBY MOORE, Manhattan Beach 
</P>
