<HEADLINE>
<P>
RAM FANS NOT EXACTLY BROKEN-HEARTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After seven season-ticket seasons with no home playoff games, after countless 
management blunders and after Georgia Frontiere's latest remarks about taking 
fan comments personally, I am compelled to quote Bugs Bunny, who said: "So long 
Screwy, see you in St. Louie!" 
</P>
<P>
 PAUL SCHOWALTER, San Dimas 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 I know all 25,705 fans can cheer gleefully and sit comfortably watching the 
Rams lose another game in their new shiny domed stadium. Georgia, I believe the 
road to the Super Bowl in your new stadium runs through St. Louis, not bankrupt 
Orange County. 
</P>
<P>
 GREGORY ALLEN HELM, President & CEO, Save the Fans, Yorba Linda 
