<HEADLINE>
<P>
WHY SHOULDN'T WEBBER GET WHAT HE WANTS? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Regarding Mark Heisler's constant bashing of Chris Webber: Mark, get over it! 
</P>
<P>
 Webber has as much right to dislike Don Nelson as we everyday working folk 
have to dislike our bosses. Webber didn't violate the conditions of his 
contract. He didn't want to stay with the Warriors just as A.C. Green didn't 
want to stay with the Lakers, so what's the problem? 
</P>
<P>
 If this event is enough to destroy millionaire Don Nelson's life, I wonder 
what he would have done if he was working for $40,000 a year at General Motors 
when the Van Nuys plant closed. 
</P>
<P>
 ERNEST WILLIAMS, Granada Hills 
</P>
