</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 East Carolina (7-4) feels it hasn't been given enough respect as a football 
independent.The biggest slap came a few weeks ago when the Pirates weren't 
invited to join a new conference that includes some of the teams in the Liberty 
Bowl alliance. 
</P>
<P>
 Today's game at Memphis, Tenn., against Illinois (6-5) gives East Carolina 
what it wants most -- an opportunity. 
</P>
<P>
 "Now it's a challenge of playing a good team and a chance to gain some 
recognition," defensive end Aaron Black said. "A lot of people don't get a 
chance to see us." 
