<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE BOWLS DAILY REPORT; COTTON / USC VS. TEXAS TECH, MONDAY; HE WOULD LOVE 
AIKMAN, SMITH OR IRVIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By EARL GUSTKEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Texas Tech offensive coordinator Dick Winder nearly burst out laughing when 
told USC Coach John Robinson had compared the style of Winder's offense to that 
of the Dallas Cowboys. 
</P>
<P>
 "I'd say we're more similar to Irons Junior High," he said."We just kind of 
draw 'em up on the sideline." 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Scrambling Texas Tech freshman quarterback Zebbie Lethridge, on his team's 
standout running back, Byron Hanspard: 
</P>
<P>
 "Byron, he's really religious. Sometimes he sings or hums religious songs in 
the huddle. He doesn't even listen to the radio." 
</P>
<P>
 USC defensive coordinator Keith Burns, on Lethridge: 
</P>
<P>
 "We listed Zebbie's strengths and weaknesses while we were deciding how to 
defend against him. His strengths filled about a page. The weaknesses were 
about two lines. 
</P>
<P>
 "He made a great play against TCU late in the first half. He scrambled, ran 
from sideline to sideline, finally found a guy in the end zone and hit him with 
a pass. We can't let him do that to us, we have to keep him in the pocket." 
EARL GUSTKEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
