<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE BOWLS DAILY REPORT; CITRUS / ALABAMA VS. OHIO STATE, MONDAY; IT WOULD TAKE 
MAGIC TO GET TICKETS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN CHERWA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ohio State quarterback Bobby Hoying tried to add an attraction to the Buckeye 
schedule when he called the Orlando Arena to try to get tickets for a Magic 
game this week. "I asked if we could get 112 tickets for Ohio State 
University?" he said."They just laughed." The Magic routinely sell out all 
games, even those against the Clippers. . . . Ohio State should be in the Rose 
Bowl hunt next year considering only 11 current players are seniors. "I think 
we'll be highly ranked next year," Ohio State Coach John Cooper said. "And if 
we win this game it will make this winter a little shorter and a little warmer 
in Columbus. Some of the young kids will have a little better work ethic." 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 A victory by Alabama in Monday's game would make the senior class the all-time 
winningest in school history. The current mark of 44-5-1 is tied with the 
1977-1980 group that went 44-4-0. "I'll remember them as a team that won 44 
games with a chance to win 45," Coach Gene Stallings said. "They won 32 games 
without getting beat. They won a national championship and averaged 11 wins a 
year. After four years, this team has had some chances to do some things. They 
had a chance to play for two national championships. A lot of teams don't have 
that chance." JOHN CHERWA 
</P>
