<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE BOWLS DAILY REPORT; FIESTA / COLORADO VS. NOTRE DAME, MONDAY; AND HE WAS 
SINGING, 'HAIL TO THE COACH' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BILL DWYRE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In 1977, Lou Holtz, now Notre Dame's football coach, was coaching at Arkansas 
and got his team into the 1978 Orange Bowl against Oklahoma.But beating 
Oklahoma was to be especially difficult, since Holtz threw four of his players 
off the team for disciplinary reasons before the game. 
</P>
<P>
 And even after Holtz's Razorbacks had pulled off a 31-6 upset, his problems 
weren't completely behind him, since the four suspended players sued him and 
the university. 
</P>
<P>
 "But it was OK, handled just fine," Holtz recalled. "I had this young Arkansas 
lawyer who took care of it just fine. Name was Bill Clinton." 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Holtz, satisfied that he has his kicking game straightened out, canceled 
Friday's practice. BILL DWYRE 
</P>
