<HEADLINE>
<P>
TV AND AFGHANISTAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 This is to express our appreciation of your information re Afghanistan in 
Howard Rosenberg's column, "Isolationist TV: Viewers Pay the Price," (Dec. 19). 
</P>
<P>
 Since the United States no longer competes with Russia for supremacy in 
Afghanistan, as you say, little or nothing is reported to us. 
</P>
<P>
 Afghanistan is ravished and conditions there, I understand, compare with any 
other country which is being destroyed by terrible warfare. We would be 
interested in knowing more about the present situation and hope there will be 
more coverage in the future. 
</P>
<P>
 ELEANOR GROSSMAN 
</P>
<P>
 La Canada 
