<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: RIDES HOME OFFERED TO DRINKING DRIVERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRISTINA LIMA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Several transportation services in Camarillo, Oxnard and Simi Valley will 
offer free rides home to drinking drivers on New Year's Eve, and towing 
companies will take drivers and their cars home. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's the type of service that needs to be done.We want to keep the streets 
and road safe for everyone," said Cindy Myers, office manager for Jim's 
Emergency Road Service in Camarillo. "Although this should not be an excuse for 
people to go out and drink." 
</P>
<P>
 The only requirements are that the cars be operable and that callers not ask 
to be taken to other parties or bars, Myers said.  
</P>
<P>
 Residents in Oxnard may contact McCarty & Sons Towing at 487-0117, while 
Camarillo residents can call Jim's Emergency Road Service at 482-1210. 
</P>
<P>
 Residents of Simi Valley who need only a ride may call EZ Shuttle and Charter 
Service at 581-1451 or Lloyd's Limousine and Van Shuttle Service at 581-5742. 
Those who need a ride and their car towed may contact Dave's Club Service at 
526-4221 and Swink's Simi Valley Towing at 522-2262. 
</P>
<P>
 In another attempt to keep the roads safe, the California Highway Patrol is 
implementing a maximum enforcement program through midnight Monday. CHRISTINA 
LIMA 
</P>
</TEXT>
