</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Alemany High could not hold a 13-point halftime lead and lost to Trinity 
(Ohio), 64-63, in the championship game of the Surf 'N' Slam girls' basketball 
tournament at La Jolla on Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Trinity, trailing, 63-59, with 33 seconds left, got a 22-foot, three-point 
shot from sophomore Semeka Randall to pull within one, then went on to win on 
Randall's fast-break layup after forcing an Alemany turnover at half 
court.Randall finished with 26 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Alemany's Samantha Rigley, who scored 20 points and had six assists, missed a 
layup in the final seconds. 
</P>
<P>
 "It was the best game I've ever been involved in," Alemany Coach Melissa 
Hearlihy said. "It was amazing. (Trinity) is easily one of the best teams in 
the country. We must of shot 80% in the first half." 
</P>
<P>
 Chrissy Falcone had 15 points for the Trojans (5-0). Kelly McKay had 18 for 
Alemany (9-2). 
</P>
<P>
 Buena 75, Olympic 20 -- Kori Sebek scored 18 points as the Bulldogs rolled in 
the consolation championship of the La Jolla tournament. Eboni Conley and 
Nicole Greathouse each added 14 points for Buena (4-2). 
</P>
<P>
 Littlerock 72, Highland 31 -- Guard Kristen Phillips scored 26 of her 32 
points in the first half for the Lobos (8-4) in the consolation championship of 
the Serrano tournament. Jasmine Vaula scored 14 points for Highland (2-5). 
