<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' SOCCER ROUNDUP; SANTA MARGARITA SHUTS OUT SADDLEBACK TO WIN ORANGE TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATT FARMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Santa Margarita saved its best for last, logging a 3-0 victory over Saddleback 
on Friday night in the final of the Orange Tournament at Chapman University. 
</P>
<P>
 "The last couple of games we've lacked intensity," Eagle Coach Curt Bauer 
said."The finals brought out the best in us." 
</P>
<P>
 The best the Eagles (13-0-1) had to offer came onthree assists from Brian 
Piesner, the diminutive forward who wreaked havoc on the Roadrunners (6-3-3). 
</P>
<P>
 Piesner found midfielder Matt Moses in front of the box at the 21-minute mark 
to give the top-ranked Eagles a 1-0 lead. He then connected with Bryce Popko 16 
minutes later to give his team a 2-0 halftime lead. 
</P>
<P>
 The Eagles slammed the door on the seventh-ranked Roadrunners three minutes 
into the second half as Piesner hit Shawn Saunders, who scored his sixth goal 
of the season. 
</P>
<P>
 "They (Piesner and midfielder Seth George) were basically the difference . . . 
they couldn't stop them," Bauer said. 
</P>
<P>
 Saddleback took three late shots, but goalkeeper Ben Froehlich preserved the 
shutout for the Eagles, who gave up one goal the entire tournament. MATT FARMER 
</P>
