<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRLS' BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; SANTA ANA BEATS REDONDO UNION TO WIN SAVANNA 
TOURNAMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Tanzenika Holmes scored 14 points to help Santa Ana defeat Redondo Beach 
Redondo Union, 47-44, Friday in the championship game of the Savanna Tournament 
at Savanna High. 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Ana (10-5) was down, 38-28, at the end of the third quarter but 
outscored Redondo Union, 19-6, in the fourth quarter.Letty Gil scored 13 for 
Santa Ana. In a third-place game: 
</P>
<P>
 La Habra 50, La Mirada 30 -- Brook Koehler was the only player to hit double 
digits for the Highlanders, scoring a game-high 18 points for La Habra (8-5). 
In consolation games: 
</P>
<P>
 El Modena 57, Sonora 31 -- Heather Potter scored 21 points for seventh-place 
El Modena (4-8). Aiyana Nash led Sonora with 23 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Bev Facey (Canada) 46, Savanna 37 -- Savanna (4-8) was led by Shauna Miller 
with 13 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Foothill 37, Buena Park 15 -- Ten players scored for the Knights (4-10) in 
their consolation-round victory. Erica Hoernig led the team in scoring with six 
points. Buena Park is 0-10. 
</P>
<P>
 Torrance 31, Cypress 25 -- Vivian Cheung and Kelly Fleishman each scored eight 
points for Cypress (6-7). In the Righetti tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Maria Righetti 54, University 44 -- Natasha Combs scored 11 points, 
including three three-pointers, and Monique Mathews had 11 points for 
University (8-3) in the championship. 
</P>
<P>
 Righetti (9-5) jumped out to a 21-3 lead in the first quarter and led, 43-19, 
after three quarters before University scored 25 points in the fourth to close 
the gap. In the Serrano Tournament 
</P>
<P>
 Whittier Christian 56, Arrowhead Christian 43 -- All-tournament selections 
Alana Kempton and Kim Menke scored 19 and 18 points to lead Whittier Christian 
(11-3), which took third place in the tournament. 
</P>
