<HEADLINE>
<P>
LAGUNA HILLS ROLLS TO WIN TOURNAMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Laguna Hills had five wrestlers advance to the final round and came away with 
four champions and 166 1/2 points to win the Montclair Invitational on Friday 
at Montclair High School. 
</P>
<P>
 Jeff Greco, ranked first in the county at 140 pounds, started the Hawks' run 
by pinning Brian Smith of Montclair in 1 minute 47 seconds. Jeff's brother Mike 
followed with a major decision, 9-0, against Gilbert Ochoa of Paramount at 145. 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Hills' Casey Elliott, at 152 pounds, scored a technical fall (21-6) 
over Jorge Huichan of Pico Rivera El Rancho and heavyweight Mark Zolikoff won, 
10-8, in overtime. 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Hills' Scott Morinoue (135) and Abel Bratton (130) placed third. 
</P>
</TEXT>
