<HEADLINE>
<P>
WATER POLO; U.S. JUNIOR TEAM DEFEATS YOUTH SQUAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The U.S. junior national team defeated the U.S. youth team, 12-9, to win the 
title in the North American Junior Water Polo Championships Friday at El Toro 
High. 
</P>
<P>
 Ryan Bailey led the junior team with five goals and Greg Mendenhall scored 
three as the junior team took an early lead and kept it throughout the game. 
</P>
<P>
 Matt Armato led the youth team with three goals. Rick McEvoy had 14 saves for 
the junior team and Greg Stoll recorded seven for the youth team. 
</P>
<P>
 In a third-place game, Canada's A team defeated Mexico's A team, 19-13. 
Mexico's B team took fifth place, beating Canada's B team, 5-4. 
</P>
</TEXT>
