<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; IN THE FULLERTON WOMEN'S BASKETBALL TOURNAMENT: 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 College of the Canyons 68, Cypress 66 -- College of the Canyons' Melissa 
Dunkerley made a pair of free throws with five seconds left to give her team 
the title. Sara Works, who was named to the all-tournament team, scored a 
game-high 21 points for Cypress (14-6). 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton 62, Compton 40 -- Lacey Sollie had 19 points and 10 rebounds, Norah 
Mariner added 14 points and 16 rebounds and Christa McDonald had 14 points and 
10 rebounds to lead Fullerton (10-9) to third place. 
</P>
<P>
 Golden West 91, American River 49 -- Julie Murdent scored 22 points, Deana 
Itow added 21 points and a career-high 14 assists and Nicole Quinn had 12 
points and 13 rebounds to lead Golden West (15-5) to a fifth-place finish. 
</P>
<P>
 Damaris McGlothin led three American River (7-8) scorers in double figures 
with 11 points. Murdent, who scored 97 points in four games, was named to the 
all-tournament team. 
</P>
