</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 U.S. Threatens China With Sanctions: Unable to resolve a dispute with China 
over intellectual property theft that targets American computer software, 
movies and tapes, the United States is preparing a list of punitive tariffs the 
Chinese warn could spark a trade war.Sources close to the negotiations said 
Friday that the threatened trade sanctions will target more than $1 billion in 
Chinese products. The goal is to force the Chinese to halt what U.S. officials 
say are abuses that cost U.S. companies $800 million annually in patent and 
copyright piracy. A formal announcement of the proposed sanctions will be made 
today by U.S. Trade Representative Mickey Kantor, according to the sources. 
