BRIEFLY: SECURITIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Nasdaq's Trading Volume Surpasses NYSE's in 1994: Posting its own historical 
high, the Nasdaq stock market in 1994 surpassed volume on the New York Stock 
Exchange for the first time, marking an important milestone on Wall 
Street.Trading volume was 74.35 billion shares on Nasdaq, 1.3% greater than the 
73.42 billion in volume on the NYSE in 1994. American Stock Exchange volume 
totaled 4.52 billion shares. Nasdaq, a global electronic trading network that 
links buyers and sellers via computer, has picked away at NYSE's dominance over 
the last several years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
