<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEW YEAR BRINGS HIGHER POSTAL PRICES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 It will cost 3 cents more to mail a letter starting Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 The U.S. Postal Service is raising rates effective at 12:01 a.m. local time, 
including raising the price of a first-class stamp to 32 cents. 
</P>
<P>
 The price to mail a post card goes up a penny, to 20 cents. 
</P>
<P>
 But the extra charge for heavy letters is unchanged. That means while the 
first ounce of a letter will cost 32 cents, each extra ounce will still mean a 
23-cent charge. 
</P>
</TEXT>
